{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-blog-markdown-remark-fields-slug-tsx","path":"/blog/solar-recap/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"solar-recap"},"html":"<p>I have had my solar panels running since the end of March, about 7 months.</p>\n<h2>App Stats</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/e60b6/TotalGeneration.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.108108108108105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"App screenshot\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/1c72d/TotalGeneration.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/a80bd/TotalGeneration.jpg 148w,\n/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/1c91a/TotalGeneration.jpg 295w,\n/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/1c72d/TotalGeneration.jpg 590w,\n/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/a8a14/TotalGeneration.jpg 885w,\n/static/3094630234c78451bba09b2be82e05e0/e60b6/TotalGeneration.jpg 1075w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>When I go away on holiday, I throttle the system down to 150w to keep the inverter cool and to avoid giving away too much power to the electricity company. Since the panels went up I have spent 5 weeks away, so the power reading should be higher again</p>\n<h2>The reality</h2>\n<p>I don't have any way of measuring the amount of the power that I have used, but I observed my electricity bill drop by about £15 a month, so not huge. Having said that, getting half of the cost back in 7 months is good going. Over the winter, the system will make much less electricity, but I will be able to use 100% of it myself.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/aea0a/HourlyElectric.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Typical daily by hour consumption\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/fcda8/HourlyElectric.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/12f09/HourlyElectric.png 148w,\n/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/e4a3f/HourlyElectric.png 295w,\n/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/fcda8/HourlyElectric.png 590w,\n/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/efc66/HourlyElectric.png 885w,\n/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/c83ae/HourlyElectric.png 1180w,\n/static/4058eb38a5e781a646fb21539f672cc7/aea0a/HourlyElectric.png 2018w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nNotice how the power consumption drops to zero during daylight hours, except lunchtime when I have the kettle/microwave running.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/01996/BestResult.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 120.27027027027026%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Best Day 2025\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/1c72d/BestResult.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/a80bd/BestResult.jpg 148w,\n/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/1c91a/BestResult.jpg 295w,\n/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/1c72d/BestResult.jpg 590w,\n/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/a8a14/BestResult.jpg 885w,\n/static/ede6bf04a4f20476eafe4485b4c836d1/01996/BestResult.jpg 1076w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nI had some days over the summer where a lot of power was made (£1.46 worth). I didn't manage to consume all the power myself, but I could add a battery in the future.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/edd00/OctoberOutput.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 94.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"October 2025\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/1c72d/OctoberOutput.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/a80bd/OctoberOutput.jpg 148w,\n/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/1c91a/OctoberOutput.jpg 295w,\n/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/1c72d/OctoberOutput.jpg 590w,\n/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/a8a14/OctoberOutput.jpg 885w,\n/static/be936e4c7d7b56fe319eb6439198d067/edd00/OctoberOutput.jpg 1074w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nEven in October there was some good power made on some days. On 24th October it made 2.56kwh, in the middle of the day, producing a 300w surplus over my home base load.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/b15c0/DailyPrices.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 91.21621621621621%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Octopus Tracker\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/1c72d/DailyPrices.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/a80bd/DailyPrices.jpg 148w,\n/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/1c91a/DailyPrices.jpg 295w,\n/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/1c72d/DailyPrices.jpg 590w,\n/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/a8a14/DailyPrices.jpg 885w,\n/static/ea239d379ee849608ac18b34c1dc2f75/b15c0/DailyPrices.jpg 1077w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nI use the Octopus Tracker energy tariff. This means the price I pay for electricity is set daily by the wind power available, so essentially if it's windy I have cheap electricity, but if it's sunny I need less power from the grid anyway.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/7f450/LiveUsage.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.810810810810814%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Home assistant widget\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/1c72d/LiveUsage.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/a80bd/LiveUsage.jpg 148w,\n/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/1c91a/LiveUsage.jpg 295w,\n/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/1c72d/LiveUsage.jpg 590w,\n/static/9e3a980f01c3fc53a5f881d2225ce094/7f450/LiveUsage.jpg 728w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nI set up home assistant and the Octopus home mini to give me real time usage. I set up a widget on my phone so I can see when the system is running in surplus so I can add load.</p>\n<h2>Next Stages</h2>\n<p>Whilst I am happy with my system, it doesn't really make enough power when it is overcast. I can fix this by adding more panels to my garage roof, but then I need a larger inverter to take more input. I am toying with the idea of getting a EcoFlow Stream X, or just adding a second small inverter with some panels attached.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"13 days ago","title":"Solar Recap","author":"Matt McCorry","tags":"solar,ecoflow"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"59f1ddca-4697-53b8-ba3c-f27b286db521","fields__slug":"solar-recap","__params":{"fields__slug":"solar-recap"}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2525421997"],"slicesMap":{}}